Made the follow-up PR: [#10832 fix(config): warn for deprecated settings from sources](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/10832).

It adds runtime warnings from `settings.toml` metadata for deprecated settings explicitly set via `[settings]` or process env, handles the `[env] MISE_TERA_V1` shim specifically, and avoids burning deprecation IDs before the logger is initialized. I also rebased after #10830 merged so the PR diff is clean.

