`warn_deprecated` returns immediately when `log::max_level()` is `Off`, but `warn_deprecated_env_settings` and `warn_deprecated_toml_settings` only run during the first `Settings::try_get()`, which `logger::init` triggers before `log::set_max_level`. Later `try_get` calls hit the cached settings and never retry, so explicit deprecated `[settings]`, process env, and `[env] MISE_TERA_V1` configs often never emit warnings in normal CLI startup.
