Addressed the PR feedback on [#10832](https://github.com/jdx/mise/pull/10832).

I fixed both review points: deprecated settings found before logger init are queued and flushed after `logger::init()`, and `warn_default_package_file_deprecated` now only bypasses its fallback when metadata actually has deprecation info. I also moved the process-env scan out of `Settings::try_get()`.

Validated with `cargo test config::settings::tests`, `cargo build`, `git diff --check`, plus smoke checks for `[settings]`, process env, and child-only `[env]` behavior. Pushed amended commit `4ac5223b2`; CI/bots are re-running.

